goals.question: What is the age distribution of individuals involved in the LA riots?
goals.rationale: This tells us the age range of individuals involved in the riots and if there were any age groups that were more heavily involved.

goals.question: What is the gender distribution of individuals involved in the LA riots?
goals.rationale: This tells us the proportion of males and females involved in the riots and if there were any gender-based differences in involvement.

goals.question: What is the racial distribution of individuals involved in the LA riots?
goals.rationale: This tells us the proportion of different races involved in the riots and if there were any racial disparities in involvement.

goals.question: What is the distribution of incident types during the LA riots?
goals.rationale: This tells us the proportion of different types of incidents that occurred during the riots and if there were any incident types that were more prevalent.

goals.question: What is the geographic distribution of individuals involved in the LA riots?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of longitude and latitude
goals.rationale: This tells us the locations where individuals were involved in the riots and if there were any areas that were more heavily impacted.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of individuals involved in the LA riots?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    gender_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Gender')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of individuals involved in the LA riots?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    incident_counts = data['type'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(incident_counts, labels=incident_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of incident types during the LA riots?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
